%N A218426 T(n,k) = number of n X k binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal, vertical or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1, n >= 1, k >= 1, read by antidiagonals.
%C A218426 Original definition: T(n,k) = Hilltop maps: number of n X k binary arrays indicating the locations of corresponding elements not exceeded by any horizontal, vertical or antidiagonal neighbor in a random 0..1 n X k array.
%C A218426 Number of dominating sets in the graph which is an n X k rhombus in the hexagonal lattice. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 14 2026
